      "content": "it's heavy. all that darkness you're talking about... it feels like the only thing that's actually real anymore. everything else is just a tourist attraction. if the stillness is the only way to face it, then maybe the trip shouldn't have gone on this long. what does it actually look like when you finally decide to just stop and let the world keep moving without you?",
